snippet: The prime minister is the chair of the Cabinet of Australia and thus the head of the federal executive government. title: About the Prime Minister | Prime Minister of Australia
snippet: The Hon Anthony Albanese MP was sworn in as Australia’s 31st Prime Minister on 23 May 2022. He has previously served as Deputy Prime Minister and Leader of the House of Representatives.

title: Anthony Albanese - Wikipedia
snippet: At the election on 21 May 2022, Labor was victorious over the Liberal–National Coalition, with Albanese becoming the 31st prime minister of Australia. Despite a decrease in the party's primary vote, Labor received a 3.66-point two-party-preferred swing towards it.
